Source: postgresql-@@PG_VERSION@@-pg-jitter
Section: database
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Vladimir Churyukin <vladich@gmail.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13),
               cmake (>= 3.16),
               g++,
               git,
               postgresql-server-dev-@@PG_VERSION@@
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Homepage: https://github.com/vladich/pg_jitter

Package: postgresql-@@PG_VERSION@@-pg-jitter
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends},
         postgresql-@@PG_VERSION@@
Description: Lightweight JIT compilation provider for PostgreSQL
 pg_jitter provides three alternative JIT backends (SLJIT, AsmJIT, MIR)
 for PostgreSQL, delivering microsecond-level compilation times instead
 of the milliseconds typical of LLVM-based JIT. Supports expression
 compilation, tuple deforming, and over 350 inlined built-in functions.
